President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Beth Cobert as the Director of the Office of Personnel Management. Cobert currently serves as the Acting Director of the Office of Personnel Management and as the Deputy Director for Management in the Office of Management and Budget. She has previously worked at McKinsey & Company, holding various leadership roles. Cobert has also served as a board member and chair of the United Way of the Bay Area and as a member of the Stanford Graduate School of Business Advisory Council. She holds a B.A. from Princeton University and an M.B.A from Stanford University Graduate School of Business. President Obama praised Cobert for her experience and commitment to serving the American people.